Description: Cylindrical hematite pendant/stamp-seal with ellipsoid base; the back has three regular grooves before the cylinder goes in to the suspension loop; the face is incised with a crescent, 2 dots, and a circle surrounding a dot.
Curator's comments: Greville John Chester acquired objects from throughout the Middle East and Egypt with little to no documentation on specific object's origins existing.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Rev Greville John Chester
